              Within the PACIOCEA area, foreign and domestic oceanic fisheries dominate the total value of production, except for New Caledonia and French Polynesia where aquaculture is significant. Coastal fishery values are usually lower than oceanic values except for Fiji, Tonga, Wallis and Futuna and Tokelau.
          </p>
